   531→### Coercion
   533→* `coerce(version, options)`: Coerces a string to semver if possible
   534→
   535→This aims to provide a very forgiving translation of a non-semver string to
   536→semver. It looks for the first digit in a string and consumes all
   537→remaining characters which satisfy at least a partial semver (e.g., `1`,
   538→`1.2`, `1.2.3`) up to the max permitted length (256 characters).  Longer
   539→versions are simply truncated (`4.6.3.9.2-alpha2` becomes `4.6.3`).  All
   540→surrounding text is simply ignored (`v3.4 replaces v3.3.1` becomes
      →…
   558→### Clean
   560→* `clean(version)`: Clean a string to be a valid semver if possible
   561→
   562→This will return a cleaned and trimmed semver version. If the provided
   563→version is not valid a null will be returned. This does not work for
   564→ranges.
   565→
   566→ex.
   567→* `s.clean(' = v 2.1.5foo')`: `null`
